description.narrative: Output 6.3: Strengthened political commitment, accountability and national capacity to legislate, plan and budget for scaling up quality rights- and gender-sensitive child protection services for vulnerable children and their families., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Protection Systems, Child Protection â€“ Strengthen Families And Communities, Data And Child Protection, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Justice For Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 6: By 2020, more children in Zimbabwe, especially adolescent girls and children without appropriate family care, are protected from violence, abuse and exploitation and benefit from improved response systems.

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF contributed to strengthened legislative, planning, and budgeting environment for child protection. UNICEF provided technical support towards the development and launch of Costed National Action Plan on Ending Child Marriages and National Disability Policy to provide for protection of children from childmarriage andtheprotectionofchildren with disability, respectively. UNICEF’s technical inputs resulted in positive reform to the Criminal Law and Codification Act on consent to sexual activity and the Public Health Act on the age of consent to accessing sexual and reproductive health services; and UNICEF supported the first Data Protection Act to be enacted. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
